 PROTECTION CIRCUITORY:

1.FUSE:
DESCRIPTION:PTC RESET FUSE 33V 750MA 1812
DATASHEET:1812L075-33DR-Littelfuse-datasheet-181956373.pdf 
Electrical Specifications
Rated Voltage (Max): 33 V DC
Holding Current (Ihold): 750 mA (0.75 A)
Trip Current (Itrip): 1.5 A
Maximum Fault Current: 20 A
Package Size: 1812 (4.5 mm × 3.2 mm) SMD
The PTC resettable fuse protects the circuit from overcurrent and short-circuit conditions. Under normal operation it allows up to 750 mA continuous current to flow. If excessive current occurs, the fuse trips by increasing its resistance and limiting the fault current. After the fault is cleared, it automatically resets, providing reusable protection for the power input and connected components. 
2.TVS DIODE:
DESCRIPTION:TVS DIODE 33V 53.3V SMB
DATASHEET:SMB 
Electrical Specifications
Working Standoff Voltage (VRWM): 33 V
Breakdown Voltage (VBR): Approximately 36.7 V – 40.6 V
Clamping Voltage (VC): 53.3 V (maximum)
Peak Pulse Power: Typically 600 W (10/1000 μs waveform)
Peak Pulse Current (IPP): Approximately 11.3 A
Package Type: SMB (Surface Mount Package)
The 33 V TVS diode protects the circuit from sudden voltage surges and transient spikes on the power input line. Under normal conditions it remains inactive and does not affect circuit operation. During an overvoltage event, it conducts heavily and clamps the voltage to about 53.3 V, preventing damage to sensitive components. It is commonly placed across the power supply input as the primary surge protection device. 
