POWER SUPPLY UNIT:
The power supply circuit uses the LM2596-5.0 buck converter to step down 24 V DC to a regulated 5 V DC output. A reverse polarity diode protects the circuit from incorrect power connections.  680 µF capacitors filter and stabilize the input voltage, while the 33 µH inductor stores and transfers energy during switching operation. The 220 µF output capacitor reduces ripple and ensures a stable 5 V supply for the load. 

1.Buck converter:
datasheet:chrome-extension://efaidnbmnnnibpcajpcglclefindmkaj/https://www.ti.com/lit/ds/symlink/lm2596.pdf
Electrical Specifications
Input Voltage Range: 4.5 V to 40 V DC
Output Voltage: Fixed 5.0 V DC
Output Current: Up to 3 A
Type: Step-Down (Buck) Switching Regulator
The LM2596-5.0 converts the 24 V DC input into a regulated 5 V DC output. It uses high-frequency switching to achieve high efficiency with low power loss. The IC controls the switching action and maintains a stable 5 V output even when the input voltage or load current changes.
2. Reverse Polarity Protection Diode
datasheet:SS34-E3-57T-Vishay-datasheet-181475108.pdf 
The diode protects the circuit if the power supply is connected with incorrect polarity. During correct operation it allows current to pass normally. If the input polarity is reversed, the diode blocks the current flow and prevents damage to the LM2596 and other components.
3. 680 µF Input Capacitor
The 680 µF capacitor at the input filters noise and voltage fluctuations from the 24 V supply. It acts as an energy reservoir and supplies transient current during switching operations. This helps maintain a stable input voltage to the buck converter.
5. Inductor
Electrical Value
Inductance: 33 µH
The inductor is the main energy storage element of the buck converter. It stores energy when the LM2596 switch is ON and releases it when the switch is OFF. This action smooths the current flow and helps reduce output voltage ripple.
6. 220 µF Output Capacitor
The 220 µF capacitor filters the output of the buck converter and reduces voltage ripple. It stores charge and delivers current during sudden load demands. This helps maintain a stable and smooth 5 V output for the connected electronics.


