The LM35DZ is used to monitor the temperature of machines, motors, transformers, control panels, and industrial equipment. It detects abnormal temperature rises caused by overload, excessive friction, poor ventilation, or component failure. When the temperature exceeds a predefined limit, the microcontroller can generate an alarm, display a warning message, send a Wi-Fi notification, or shut down the equipment to prevent damage.
Opto-Isolation Circuit – PC817X1J000F Optocoupler

Datasheet:pc817xj0000f_e 
Electrical Specifications
Component Type: Optocoupler / Photocoupler
Isolation Voltage: 5 kVrms
Input LED Forward Voltage: 1.2 V (typical)
Maximum Input LED Current: 50 mA
Output Type: Phototransistor
Maximum Collector-Emitter Voltage: 80 V
